goals.visualization: scatter plot of longitude and latitude
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of capital cities across the United States and identify any patterns or clusters.

goals.question: Which state has the highest number of capital cities?
goals.visualization: bar chart of number of capital cities per state
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the states with the most and least number of capital cities and understand any potential reasons for the distribution.

goals.question: What is the average longitude and latitude of all capital cities?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of all capital cities with average longitude and latitude marked
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the central tendency of the capital cities and identify any outliers.

goals.question: What is the distribution of longitude and latitude within each state?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of longitude and latitude for each state
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of capital cities within each state and identify any patterns or clusters.

goals.question: What is the most common first letter of the capital city names?
goals.visualization: bar chart of count of capital city names by first letter
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify any potential naming conventions or patterns across the capital cities.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['lon'], data['lat'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude across all capital cities?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    state_counts = data['state'].value_counts()
    state_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("Which state has the highest number of capital cities?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    avg_lon = np.mean(data['lon'])
    avg_lat = np.mean(data['lat'])
    
    plt.scatter(data['lon'], data['lat'], label='Capital Cities')
    plt.axvline(avg_lon, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Avg Longitude: {avg_lon:.2f}')
    plt.axhline(avg_lat, color='g', linestyle='--', label=f'Avg Latitude: {avg_lat:.2f}')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average longitude and latitude of all capital cities?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['first_letter'] = data['city'].apply(lambda x: x[0].upper())
    letter_counts = data['first_letter'].value_counts()
    
    ax = letter_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the most common first letter of the capital city names?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
